                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51 Salt Funds/96: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-30T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 30, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 30—8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>391. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 30, 2 p.m. Supplementing my March 29, midnight,<note n="36"
                                xml:id="d688fn36">Not printed.</note> Japanese press reports that
                            new government announced on the 28th that the Salt Administration is
                            hereafter independent of Nanking and that all of its administrative
                            functions will be taken over by Changchun; that foreign obligations
                            secured by the Salt Gabelle will not be repudiated and claims entered by
                            the creditor powers will be considered; and that employees willing to
                            sever connections with the Chinese Government will be retained.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
